OL,6,FThe ODPA's investigation identified
OL,7,Fthat Jacksons employees had amended
OL,8,Fcustomer records, changing their
OL,9,Fdirect marketing preferences from 'No'
OL,10,Fto 'Yes'.
OL,12,FThis resulted in 430 customers
OL,13,Freceiving direct marketing
OL,14,Fcommunications against their will.
OL,16,FAn internal review by Jacksons
OL,17,Festablished that this had been done by
OL,18,Fcertain sales staff at the direction
OL,19,Fof a senior staff member who is no
OL,20,Flonger employed by the company.
